children.subject: I wouldn't sweat it too much, the workload isn't too different. I would mainly consider the upper divs you can take: for example, if you wanted to take 170 asap you might consider taking 70 earlier so you can take 170 by the spring. vice versa for 16B and EE 120, as an example.

history.content:
Hi everyone, I'm a rising EECS sophomore and currently taking cs61a, ee16a, math53, and r&c. I need some advice on my class schedule for the coming fall, spring semester. My schedule is:
Fall 2021: cs61b, ee16b, physics 7a, and a breath
Spring 2022: cs61c, cs70, physics 7b, and considering a breath
Just wondering if I should interchange ee16b with cs70 since I saw a lot of people stating cs61c and cs70 is pretty high workload in a semester. However, some people said I will lost priority in ee16b if I take it in spring (not sure if this is true). Any useful advice??
Thanks in advance! :)
history.subject: Schedule Advice
